OIL WELL SUPPLY COMPANY, Substituted in the Place and Stead of Daniel G. Tomlinson, Appellant, v. Robert BROMBERG, as Trustee of J. R. M. Kimball, Doing Business as COMMUNITY MONARCH PETROLEUM COMPANY OF CALIFORNIA, Bankrupt, Appellee. No. 6840. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 12, 1932. Cressaty & Elstein, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Raphael Deehter and Joseph Rifkind, both of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges, and NETERER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for appellant, ' consented to by counsel for appellee, ordered appeal herein dismissed; mandate forthwith.
